<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">(312) <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">588-4110&nbsp;Foreign</FONT> TDD line for hearing impaired </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>How many shares must be present to conduct business at the Annual Meeting? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">To carry on the business of the Annual Meeting, a minimum number of shares, constituting a quorum, must be present, either in person or by proxy. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">On most matters, the votes of the holders of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock are counted together. However, there are some matters that must be voted on only by the holders of one class of stock. We will
have a quorum for all matters to be voted on at the Annual Meeting if the following number of votes is present, in person or by proxy: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>For any matter requiring the vote of the Common Stock voting separately:</I>&nbsp;a majority of the votes of the Common Stock outstanding on the Record Date. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>For any matter requiring the vote of the Class</I><I></I><I>&nbsp;B Common Stock voting separately:</I>&nbsp;a majority of the votes of the Class&nbsp;B Common Stock outstanding on the Record Date. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>For any matter requiring the vote of the Common Stock and Class</I><I></I><I>&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together without regard to class:</I>&nbsp;a majority of the votes of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common
Stock outstanding on the Record Date. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">It is possible that we could have a quorum for certain items of business to be voted on at the Annual Meeting and not have a quorum for other matters. If that occurs, we will proceed with a vote only on the matters for
which a quorum is present. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>What vote is required to approve each proposal? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Assuming that a quorum is present: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Proposal No.</I><I></I><I>&nbsp;1:</I><I></I><I>&nbsp;Election of Directors</I>&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;the two nominees to be elected by holders of our Common Stock voting separately as a class who receive the greatest
number of votes cast &#147;FOR,&#148; and the nine nominees to be elected by holders of our Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together who receive the greatest number of votes cast &#147;FOR,&#148; will be elected as directors.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Proposal No.</I><I></I><I>&nbsp;2: Ratification of the Appointment of Ernst</I><I></I><I>&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as Independent Auditors</I>&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;the affirmative vote of the holders of at least a majority
of the shares of Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock (voting together as a class) represented at the Annual Meeting. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">9 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Proposal No.</I><I></I><I>&nbsp;3: Advise on Named Executive Officer Compensation</I>&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;the affirmative vote of the holders of at least a majority of the shares of Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common
Stock (voting together as a class) represented at the Annual Meeting. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Are abstentions and broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> counted in the vote totals? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Abstentions are counted as being present and entitled to vote in determining whether a quorum is present. Shares as to which broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> exist will be counted as present and
entitled to vote in determining whether a quorum is present for any matter requiring the vote of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together as a class, but they will not be counted as present and entitled to vote in determining
whether a quorum is present for any matter requiring the vote of the Common Stock or Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting separately as a class. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If you mark or vote &#147;abstain&#148; on Proposal Nos.&nbsp;2 or 3, the abstention will have the effect of being counted as a vote &#147;AGAINST&#148; the proposal. Broker
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> with respect to Proposal <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Nos.&nbsp;1-3</FONT> are not included in vote totals and will not affect the outcome of the vote on those proposals. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Who will pay the cost of soliciting votes for the Annual Meeting? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We will pay the cost of preparing, assembling and furnishing proxy solicitation and other required Annual Meeting materials. We do not use a third-party solicitor. It is possible that our directors, officers and
employees might solicit proxies by mail, telephone, telefax, electronically over the Internet or by personal contact, without receiving additional compensation. We will reimburse brokers, banks and other nominees, fiduciaries and custodians who
nominally hold shares of our stock as of the Record Date for the reasonable costs they incur furnishing proxy solicitation and other required Annual Meeting materials to street-name holders who beneficially own those shares on the Record Date.
</TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">10 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_9"></A>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We have a long-standing commitment to good corporate governance practices. Our corporate governance policies and other documents establish the high standards
of professional and personal conduct we expect of our Board, members of senior management and all employees, and promote compliance with various financial, ethical, legal and other obligations and responsibilities. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The business activities of the Company are carried out by our employees under the direction and supervision of our President and Chief Executive Officer
(&#147;CEO&#148;). The Board is responsible for overseeing these activities. In doing so, each director is required to use his or her business judgment in the best interests of the Company. The Board&#146;s responsibilities include: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reviewing the Company&#146;s performance, strategies and major decisions; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing the Company&#146;s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements and the integrity of its financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing the Company&#146;s policies and practices for identifying, managing and mitigating key enterprise risks; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing management, including reviewing the CEO&#146;s performance and succession planning for key management roles; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing executive and director compensation, and our compensation program and policies. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
 COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Corporate Governance Guidelines </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has adopted Corporate Governance Guidelines that, along with the charters of the Board committees, provide the basic framework for the Board&#146;s
operation and role in the governance of the Company. The guidelines include the Board&#146;s policies regarding director independence, qualifications and responsibilities, access to management and outside advisors, compensation, continuing
education, oversight of management succession and stockholding requirements. They also provide a process for directors to annually evaluate the performance of the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Governance Committee is responsible for overseeing and reviewing the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines at least annually and recommending any
proposed changes to the Board for approval. The Corporate Governance Guidelines are available on the Investors section of our website at <I>www.thehersheycompany.com.</I> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Code of Conduct </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has adopted a Code of Conduct that applies
to all of our directors, officers and employees worldwide. Adherence to this Code of Conduct assures that our directors, officers and employees are held to the highest standards of integrity. The Code of Conduct covers areas such as conflicts of
interest, insider trading and compliance with laws and regulations. The Audit Committee oversees the Company&#146;s communication of, and compliance with, the Code of Conduct. The Code of Conduct, including amendments thereto or waivers granted to a
director or officer, if any, can be viewed on the Investors section of our website at <I>www.thehersheycompany.com.</I> </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">11 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Stockholder and Interested Party Communications with Directors </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Stockholders and other interested parties may
communicate with our directors in several ways. Communications regarding accounting, internal accounting controls or auditing matters may be emailed to the Audit Committee at auditcommittee@hersheys.com or addressed to the Audit Committee at the
following address: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Audit Committee </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">c/o Corporate Secretary </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The
Hershey Company </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">100 Crystal A Drive </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">P.O. Box 810 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Hershey, PA
17033-0810 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Stockholders and other interested parties also can submit comments, confidentially and anonymously if desired, to the Audit Committee by
calling the Hershey Concern Line at <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(800)&nbsp;362-8321</FONT> or by accessing the Hershey Concern Line website at <I>www.HersheysConcern.com</I>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Stockholders and other interested parties may contact any of the independent directors, including the Lead Independent Director, as well as the independent
directors as a group, by writing to the specified party at the address set forth above or by emailing the independent directors (or a specific independent director, including the Lead Independent Director) at independentdirectors@hersheys.com.
Stockholders and other interested parties may also contact any of the independent directors using the Hershey Concern Line telephone number or website noted above. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Communications to the Audit Committee, any of the independent directors and the Hershey Concern Line are processed by the Office of General Counsel. The Office
of General Counsel reviews and summarizes these communications and provides reports to the applicable party on a periodic basis. Communications regarding any accounting, internal control or auditing matter are reported immediately to the Audit
Committee, as are allegations about our officers. The Audit Committee will address communications from any interested party in accordance with our Board-approved Procedures for Submission and Handling of Complaints Regarding Compliance Matters,
which are available for viewing on the Investors section of our website at <I>www.thehersheycompany.com</I>. Solicitations, junk mail and obviously frivolous or inappropriate communications are not forwarded to the Audit Committee or the independent
directors, but copies are retained and made available to any director who wishes to review them. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Director Independence
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board, in consultation with the
Governance Committee, determines which of our directors are independent. The Board has adopted categorical standards for independence that the Board uses in determining which directors are independent. The Board bases its determination of
independence for each director on the more stringent independence standards applicable to Audit Committee members regardless of whether such director serves on the Audit Committee. These standards are contained in the Board&#146;s Corporate
Governance Guidelines. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">12 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Applying these categorical standards for independence, as well as the independence requirements set forth in
the listing standards of the New York Stock Exchange (the &#147;NYSE Rules&#148;) and the rules and regulations of the Securities and Exchange Commission (&#147;SEC&#148;), the Board determined that the following directors recommended for election
at the Annual Meeting are independent: Pamela&nbsp;M. Arway, James W. Brown, Charles&nbsp;A.&nbsp;Davis, Mary&nbsp;Kay&nbsp;Haben, James C. Katzman, M. Diane Koken, Robert&nbsp;M.&nbsp;Malcolm, Anthony&nbsp;J.&nbsp;Palmer,
Wendy&nbsp;L.&nbsp;Schoppert and David&nbsp;L.&nbsp;Shedlarz. In addition, the Board determined the following directors who served in 2017 were independent: Robert F. Cavanaugh, James M. Mead, James E. Nevels and Thomas J. Ridge. The Board
determined that John&nbsp;P.&nbsp;Bilbrey is not independent because he served as an executive officer of the Company until March&nbsp;1, 2017, and that Michele&nbsp;G.&nbsp;Buck is not independent because she is an executive officer of the Company.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In making its independence determinations, the Board, in consultation with the Governance Committee, reviewed the direct and indirect relationships
between each director and the Company and its subsidiaries, as well as the compensation and other payments each director received from or made to the Company and its subsidiaries. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In making its independence determinations with respect to Ms.&nbsp;Koken and Messrs. Brown and Katzman, the Board considered their roles as current members of
the board of directors of Hershey Trust Company and the board of managers (governing body) of Milton Hershey School, as well as certain transactions the Company had or may have with these entities. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the trust established by Milton S. and Catherine S. Hershey that has as its sole beneficiary Milton Hershey School (such
trust, the &#147;Milton Hershey School Trust&#148;), is our controlling stockholder. Hershey Trust Company is in turn owned by the Milton Hershey School Trust. As such, Hershey Trust Company, Milton Hershey School, the Milton Hershey School Trust
and companies owned by the Milton Hershey School Trust are considered affiliates of the Company under SEC rules. During 2017, we had a number of transactions with Hershey Trust Company, Milton Hershey School and companies owned by the Milton Hershey
School Trust involving the purchase and sale of goods and services in the ordinary course of business and the leasing of real estate at market rates. We have outlined these transactions in greater detail in the section entitled &#147;Certain
Transactions and Relationships.&#148; We have provided information about Company stock owned by Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust, and by Hershey Trust Company for its own investment purposes in the section
entitled &#147;Information Regarding Our Controlling Stockholder.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Ms.&nbsp;Koken and Messrs. Brown and Katzman do not receive any compensation from
The Hershey Company, from Hershey Trust Company or from Milton Hershey School other than compensation they receive or will receive in the ordinary course as members of the board of directors or board of managers of each of those entities, as
applicable. In addition, Ms.&nbsp;Koken and Messrs. Brown and Katzman do not vote on Board decisions in connection with the Company&#146;s transactions with Hershey Trust Company, Milton Hershey School and companies owned by the Milton Hershey
School Trust. The Board therefore concluded that the positions Ms.&nbsp;Koken and Messrs. Brown and Katzman have as members of the board of directors of Hershey Trust Company and the board of managers of Milton Hershey School do not impact their
independence. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Director Nominations </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Governance Committee is responsible for
identifying and recommending to the Board candidates for Board membership. As our controlling stockholder, Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust, also may from time to time recommend to the Governance Committee, or
elect outright, individuals to serve on our Board. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">13 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In administering its responsibilities, the Governance Committee has not adopted formal selection procedures,
but instead utilizes general guidelines that allow it to adjust the selection process to best satisfy the objectives established for any director search. The Governance Committee considers director candidates recommended by any reasonable source,
including current directors, management, stockholders (including Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust) and other sources. The Governance Committee evaluates all director candidates in the same manner, regardless of
the source of the recommendation. The Governance Committee has established a policy that it will not recommend a candidate to the full Board until all members of the Governance Committee have interviewed and approved the candidate for nomination.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Occasionally, the Governance Committee engages a paid third-party consultant to assist in identifying and evaluating director candidates. The Governance
Committee has sole authority under its charter to retain, compensate and terminate these consultants. In 2017, the Governance Committee retained Egon Zehnder to assist in identifying potential future director candidates as several current directors
approach their 72<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">nd</SUP> birthday. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Stockholders desiring to recommend or nominate a director candidate
must comply with certain procedures. If you are a stockholder and desire to nominate a director candidate at the 2019 Annual Meeting of Stockholders of the Company, you must comply with the procedures for nomination set forth in the section entitled
&#147;Information Regarding the 2019 Annual Meeting of Stockholders.&#148; Stockholders who do not intend to nominate a director at an annual meeting may recommend a director candidate to the Governance Committee for consideration at any time.
Stockholders desiring to do so must submit their recommendation in writing to The Hershey Company, c/o Corporate Secretary, 100 Crystal A Drive, Hershey, Pennsylvania 17033-0810, and include in the submission all of the information that would be
required if the stockholder nominated the candidate at an annual meeting. The Governance Committee may require the nominating stockholder to submit additional information before considering the candidate. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">There were no changes to the procedures relating to stockholder nominations during 2017, and there have been no changes to such procedures to date in 2018.
These procedural requirements are intended to ensure the Governance Committee has sufficient time and a basis on which to assess potential director candidates and are not intended to discourage or interfere with appropriate stockholder nominations.
The Governance Committee does not believe that these procedural requirements subject any stockholder or proposed nominee to unreasonable burdens. The Governance Committee and the Board reserve the right to change the procedural requirements from
time to time and/or to waive some or all of the requirements with respect to certain nominees, but any such waiver shall not preclude the Governance Committee from insisting upon compliance with any and all of the above requirements by any other
recommending stockholder or proposed nominees. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">14 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_10"></A>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>General Oversight </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has general oversight responsibility for the
Company&#146;s affairs. Although the Board does not have responsibility for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">day-to-day</FONT></FONT> management of the Company, Board members stay informed about the Company&#146;s
business through regular meetings, site visits and other periodic interactions with management. The Board is deeply involved in the Company&#146;s strategic planning process. The Board also plays an important oversight role in the Company&#146;s
leadership development and succession planning processes. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Composition </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board is currently comprised of 13 members, each
serving a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-year</FONT> term that expires at the Annual Meeting. Ten of the 11 director nominees are considered independent under the NYSE Rules and the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Leadership Structure </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Company&#146;s governance documents provide the
Board with flexibility to select the leadership structure that is most appropriate for the Company and its stockholders. The Board regularly evaluates its governance structure and has concluded that the Company and its stockholders are best served
by not having a formal policy regarding whether the same individual should serve as both Chairman of the Board and CEO. This approach allows the Board to exercise its business judgment in determining the most appropriate leadership structure in
light of the current facts and circumstances facing the Company, including the composition and tenure of the Board, the tenure of the CEO, the strength of the Company&#146;s management team, the Company&#146;s recent financial performance, the
Company&#146;s current strategic plan and the current economic environment, among other factors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Effective March&nbsp;1, 2017, the Board split the roles
of Chairman of the Board and CEO, with Michele&nbsp;G.&nbsp;Buck assuming responsibility as President and CEO and John P.&nbsp;Bilbrey transitioning to the role of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board recognizes the importance of strong independent Board leadership. Although no longer serving as an executive officer of the Company, Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey
is not independent due to his prior service as CEO. For that reason, Charles A. Davis currently serves as Lead Independent Director, a position he has held since May 2017. Having served on the Board since November 2007, Mr.&nbsp;Davis&#146;s service
helps ensure continuity of independent Board leadership as well as effective communication between the CEO, the Chairman of the Board and the independent directors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Under the terms of the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the Lead Independent Director&#146;s responsibilities include the following: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In the absence of the Chairman of the Board, presiding at all Board and stockholder meetings; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Calling meetings of the independent directors of the Board, in addition to the executive sessions of independent directors held during each Board meeting; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Establishing the agenda and presiding at all executive sessions and other meetings of the independent directors of the Board; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Communicating with the independent directors of the Board between meetings as necessary or appropriate; </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">15 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Serving as a liaison between the Chairman of the Board and the independent directors, ensuring independent director consensus is communicated to the Chairman of the Board, and communicating the results of meetings of
the independent directors to the Chairman of the Board and members of management, as appropriate; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Approving Board meeting agendas and schedules to assure there is sufficient time for discussion of all agenda items; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Approving Board meeting materials and other information sent to the Board; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Evaluating the quality and timeliness of information sent to the Board by the CEO and other members of management; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Assisting the Chairman of the Board on matters of Board succession planning and crisis management; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing the evaluation of the CEO; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Assisting the chair of the Governance Committee with Board and individual director evaluations; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Being available for consultation and direct communication at the request of major stockholders. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has
determined that Mr.&nbsp;Davis is an independent member of the Board under the NYSE Rules and the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mr.
Bilbrey is not standing for re-election as a director at the Annual Meeting. Pursuant to the terms&nbsp;of&nbsp;the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the directors have elected Mr. Davis to succeed Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey as Chairman of the
Board upon expiration of Mr. Bilbrey&#146;s term, subject to Mr. Davis&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> as a director at the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has established five standing committees to assist with its oversight responsibilities: (1)&nbsp;Audit Committee; (2)&nbsp;Compensation and Executive
Organization Committee (&#147;Compensation Committee&#148;); (3)&nbsp;Finance and Risk Management Committee; (4)&nbsp;Governance Committee; and (5)&nbsp;Executive Committee. Each of the Audit Committee, the Compensation Committee, the Finance and
Risk Management Committee, and the Governance Committee is comprised entirely of independent directors. Finally, Mr.&nbsp;Brown and Ms.&nbsp;Koken are direct representatives of the Company&#146;s largest stockholder. This composition of our Board
helps to ensure that boardroom discussions reflect the views of management, our independent directors and our stockholders. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Board Role in Risk Oversight </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our Board takes an active role in risk oversight.
While management is responsible for identifying, evaluating, managing and mitigating the Company&#146;s exposure to risk, it is the Board&#146;s responsibility to oversee the Company&#146;s risk management process and to ensure that management is
taking appropriate action to identify, manage and mitigate key risks. The Board administers its risk oversight responsibilities both through active review and discussion of key risks facing the Company and by delegating certain risk oversight
responsibilities to committees for further consideration and evaluation. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">16 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following table summarizes the role of the Board and each of its committees in overseeing risk: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #999999; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff">Role&nbsp;in&nbsp;Risk&nbsp;Oversight</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Regularly reviews and evaluates the Company&#146;s strategic plans and associated risks.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees the
Company&#146;s enterprise risk management (&#147;ERM&#148;) framework and the overall ERM process.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Conducts annual succession plan reviews to ensure the Company maintains appropriate succession
plans for members of senior management.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees compliance with legal and regulatory requirements and the Company&#146;s Code of
Conduct.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees
risks relating to key accounting policies.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews internal controls with the Principal Financial Officer, Principal Accounting Officer
and internal auditors.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Meets regularly with representatives of the Company&#146;s independent auditors.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Compensation and</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Executive
Organization</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Committee</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees risks relating to the Company&#146;s compensation program and policies.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees the process
for conducting annual risk assessments of the Company&#146;s compensation policies and practices.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Employs independent compensation consultants to assist in reviewing the Company&#146;s
compensation program, including the potential risks created by such program.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees the Company&#146;s succession planning and talent processes and programs.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Finance and Risk</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Management
Committee</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews enterprise-level and other key risks identified through the Company&#146;s ERM process
as well as management&#146;s plans to mitigate those risks.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees key financial risks.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees and approves
proposed merger and acquisition activities and related risks.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Chair meets at least annually with the Audit Committee to discuss the Company&#146;s risk
management programs.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Governance Committee</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees risks relating to the Company&#146;s governance structure and other corporate
governance matters and processes.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees compliance with key corporate governance documents, including the Corporate
Governance Guidelines and the Insider Trading Policy.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Executive Committee</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews and approves, through a special committee of independent directors on the Executive
Committee, any related party transactions between the Company and entities affiliated with the Company and certain of its directors.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">17 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The decision to administer the Board&#146;s oversight responsibilities in this manner has an important
effect on the Board&#146;s leadership and committee structure, described in more detail above. The Board believes that its structure&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;including a strong Lead Independent Director, 10 of 11 independent directors and key committees
comprised entirely of independent directors&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;helps to ensure that key strategic decisions made by senior management, up to and including the CEO, are reviewed and overseen by independent directors of the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Experiences, Skills and Qualifications </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Governance Committee works with the Board to
determine the appropriate characteristics, skills and experiences that should be possessed by the Board as a whole as well as its individual members. While the Governance Committee has not established minimum criteria for director candidates, in
general, the Board seeks individuals with skills and backgrounds that will complement those of other directors and maximize the diversity and effectiveness of the Board as a whole. The Board also seeks individuals who bring unique and varied
perspectives and life experiences to the Board. As such, the Governance Committee assists the Board by recommending prospective director candidates who will enhance the overall diversity of the Board. The Board views diversity broadly, taking into
consideration the age, professional experience, race, education, gender and other attributes of its members. In addition, the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines describe the general experiences, qualifications, attributes and skills sought
by the Board of any director nominee, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

Skills</FONT></B></FONT></TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.33em; text-indent:-1.33em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003; Overall desirability as an addition to the Board and its committees</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.33em; text-indent:-1.33em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003; &nbsp;Government, public policy and regulatory affairs</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In addition to evaluating new director candidates, the Governance Committee regularly assesses the composition of the Board in
order to ensure it reflects an appropriate balance of knowledge, skills, expertise, diversity and independence. As part of this assessment, each director is asked to identify and assess the particular experiences, skills and other attributes that
qualify him or her to serve as a member of the Board. Based on the most recent assessment of the Board&#146;s composition completed in February 2018, the Governance Committee and the Board have determined that, in light of the Company&#146;s current
business structure and strategies, the Board has an appropriate mix of director experiences, skills, qualifications and backgrounds. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A description of the
most relevant experiences, skills, attributes and qualifications that qualify each director nominee to serve as a member of the Board is included in his or her biography. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">18 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_11"></A>MEETINGS AND COMMITTEES OF THE BOARD
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Meetings of the Board of Directors and Director Attendance at Annual Meeting </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board held 12 meetings in 2017. Each incumbent
director attended at least 82% of all of the meetings of the Board and committees of the Board on which he or she served in 2017, except for Ms.&nbsp;Koken, who was unable to attend two meetings due to scheduling conflicts known prior to her
election as a director in 2017, and Mr.&nbsp;Ridge, who was unable to attend several meetings due to health-related matters. Average director attendance for all meetings equaled 88%. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In addition, the independent directors meet regularly in executive session at every Board meeting and at other times as the independent directors deem
necessary. These meetings allow the independent directors to discuss important issues, including the business and affairs of the Company as well as matters concerning management, without any member of management present. Each executive session is
chaired by the Lead Independent Director. In the absence of the Lead Independent Director, executive sessions are chaired by an independent director assigned on a rotating basis. Members of the Audit Committee, Compensation Committee, Finance and
Risk Management Committee, and Governance Committee also meet regularly in executive session. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Directors are expected to attend our annual meetings of
stockholders. Eleven of the twelve directors standing for election at the 2017 Annual Meeting of Stockholders of the Company attended that meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
 COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Committees of the Board </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has established five standing committees. Membership on each of these committees, as of March&nbsp;5, 2018, is shown in the following chart: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Name</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:5pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines require that every member of the Audit Committee,
Compensation Committee, Finance and Risk Management Committee, and Governance Committee be independent. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board may also from time to time establish
committees of limited duration for a special purpose. No such committees were established in 2017. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The table below identifies the number of meetings held
by each standing committee in 2017, provides a brief description of the duties and responsibilities of each committee, and provides general information regarding the location of each committee&#146;s charter: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="81%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Committee</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Audit</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Meetings</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">7</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Duties and Responsibilities&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee the Company&#146;s financial reporting processes and the integrity of the
Company&#146;s financial statements.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee the Company&#146;s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee the performance
of the Company&#146;s independent auditors and the internal audit function.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Approve all audit and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services and fees.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee (in consultation
with the Finance and Risk Management Committee) the Company&#146;s risk management processes and policies.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review the adequacy of internal controls.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and discuss with
management Quarterly Reports on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-Q</FONT> and Annual Report on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Form&nbsp;10-K</FONT> prior to filing with the SEC.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and discuss with
management earnings releases.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Administer the Company&#146;s Procedures for Submission and Handling of Complaints Regarding
Compliance Matters.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>General Information</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board has determined that all directors on the Audit Committee are financially literate.
The Board has also determined that Messrs. Mead, Palmer and Shedlarz and Ms.&nbsp;Schoppert qualify as&nbsp;&#147;audit committee financial experts&#148; as defined in SEC regulations and that each has accounting or related financial management
expertise.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Charter
can be viewed on the Investors section of our website at<I></I><I>&nbsp;www.thehersheycompany.com.</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Charter prohibits any member of the Audit Committee from serving on the audit committees of
more than two other public companies unless the Board determines that such simultaneous service would not impair the ability of the director to effectively serve&nbsp;on the Committee.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">
