<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="81%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Committee</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Compensation and Executive Organization</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Meetings</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">9</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Duties and Responsibilities&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Establish executive officer compensation (other than CEO compensation) and oversee the
compensation program and policies for all executive officers.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluate the performance of the CEO and make recommendations to the independent directors of
the Board regarding CEO compensation.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and recommend to the Board the form and amount of director compensation.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Make equity grants under
and administer the Company&#146;s Equity and Incentive Compensation Plan (the &#147;EICP&#148;).</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Establish target award levels and make awards under the annual cash incentive component of the
EICP.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitor
executive compensation arrangements for consistency with corporate objectives and stockholders&#146; interests.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review the executive organization of the Company.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitor the development
of personnel available to fill key executive positions as part of the succession planning process.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>General Information</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Charter can be viewed on the Investors section of our website
at<I></I><I>&nbsp;www.thehersheycompany.com.</I></P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recommend to the Board
the terms of the Company&#146;s principal banking relationships, credit facilities and commercial paper programs.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee (in consultation with the Audit Committee) the Company&#146;s risk management processes
and policies.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and make recommendations on the composition of the Board and its committees.</P>

including the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Administer the Company&#146;s Related Person Transaction Policy as directed by the Board.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluate the performance
of the Board, its independent committees and each director.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Executive</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Meetings</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">0</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Duties and Responsibilities&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Manage the business and affairs of the Company, to the extent permitted by the Delaware General
Corporation Law, when the Board is not in session.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and approve, through a subcommittee consisting of the independent directors on the
Executive Committee who are not affiliated with Hershey Trust Company, Hershey Entertainment&nbsp;&amp; Resorts Company and/or Milton Hershey School, or any of their affiliates, any transaction not in the ordinary course of business between the
Company and any of these entities, unless otherwise provided by the Board or the Corporate Governance Guidelines.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Currently, the Corporate Governance Guidelines provide that, unless directed otherwise by the
independent members of the Board who have no affiliation with any of the above entities, such transactions will be reviewed and approved in advance by a special committee consisting of the directors elected by the holders of our Common Stock voting
separately, and only in the absence of such directors will the subcommittee of the Executive Committee approve such transactions.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>General Information</B></FONT></P></TD>

at<I></I><I>&nbsp;www.thehersheycompany.com.</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

transactions, please refer to the section entitled &#147;Certain Transactions and Relationships.&#148;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">22 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_12"></A>PROPOSAL NO. 1&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;ELECTION
OF DIRECTORS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:40pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="90%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt" COLOR="#3f000b">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt" COLOR="#3f000b">&#10003;</FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt" COLOR="#3f000b">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#3f000b" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#3f000b">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">The Board of Directors unanimously recommends that stockholders<BR>vote
<B>FOR</B> each of the nominees for director at the<BR>2018 Annual Meeting</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The first proposal to be voted on at the Annual Meeting is the election of 11 directors. If elected, the directors will hold
office until the 2019 Annual Meeting of Stockholders of the Company or until their successors are elected and qualified. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Election Procedures </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We have two classes of common stock outstanding:
Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock. Under our certificate of incorporation and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">by-laws:</FONT> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">One-sixth</FONT> of the total number of our directors (which equates presently to two directors) will be elected by the holders of our Common Stock voting separately as a class. For the
2018 Annual Meeting, the Board has nominated Mary Kay Haben and Wendy&nbsp;L. Schoppert for election by the holders of our Common Stock voting separately as a class. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The remaining nine directors will be elected by the holders of our Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together without regard to class. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">With respect to the nominees to be elected by the holders of the Common Stock and the Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together, the nine nominees receiving
the greatest number of votes of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock will be elected as directors. With respect to the nominees to be elected by the holders of the Common Stock voting separately as a class, the two nominees receiving the
greatest number of votes of the Common Stock will be elected as directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines provide that directors will
generally not be nominated for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> after their 72<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">nd</SUP> birthday. All of the directors standing for election at the 2018 Annual Meeting satisfied the
applicable age requirement at the time of their nomination. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">All nominees for election as director have indicated their willingness to serve if elected. If
a nominee becomes unavailable for election for any reason, the proxies will have discretionary authority to vote for a substitute. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Nominees for Director </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board unanimously recommends the following
nominees for election at the 2018 Annual Meeting. These nominees were recommended to the Board by the Governance Committee. In making its recommendation, the Governance Committee considered the experience, qualifications, attributes and skills of
each nominee, as well as each director&#146;s past performance on our Board, as reflected in the Governance Committee&#146;s annual evaluation of Board and committee performance. This evaluation considers, among other things, each director&#146;s
individual contributions to the Board, the director&#146;s ability to work collaboratively with other directors and the effectiveness of the Board as a whole. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Messrs. Bilbrey, Mead and Ridge are not standing for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> at the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On the following pages, we provide certain biographical information about each nominee for director, as well as information regarding the nominee&#146;s
specific experience, qualifications, attributes and skills that qualify him or her to serve as a director and as a member of the committee(s) of the Board on which the nominee serves. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">23 </P>

</DIV></Center>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">One of three representatives of Hershey Trust Company and Milton Hershey School being nominated to serve on the Board, Mr. Brown provides valuable

familiarity with policy and operations of both Pennsylvania State and U.S. Federal Government and his experience as an investor in and director of both public and private companies make him an important addition to the Board on matters of strategy
and risk management.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

 COLOR="#3f000b"><B><I>PREVIOUS BUSINESS EXPERIENCE</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

insurance, risk management and regulatory affairs. Her experience in the areas of legal operations and corporate governance, developed throughout her 22-year career at a national life insurer that culminated in her serving as Vice President, General

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_13"></A><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">NON-EMPLOYEE</FONT> DIRECTOR COMPENSATION </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>The Hershey Company Directors&#146; Compensation Plan </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We maintain a Directors&#146; Compensation Plan that is designed to: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Attract and retain highly qualified, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align the interests of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors with those of our stockholders by paying a portion of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> compensation in units
representing shares of our Common Stock. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Directors who are employees of the Company receive no additional compensation for their service on
our Board. Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey, our current Chairman of the Board, who retired from the position of President and CEO on March&nbsp;1, 2017, received no additional compensation for his Board service while he was an employee of the Company.
Ms.&nbsp;Buck, who became our President and CEO and was appointed to the Board on March&nbsp;1, 2017, received no additional compensation for her Board service. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board targets <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation at the 50<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP>
percentile of compensation paid to directors at a peer group of companies we call the 2017 Peer Group. Information about the 2017 Peer Group is included in the section entitled &#147;Setting Compensation&#148; in the Compensation
Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis. Each year, with the assistance of the Compensation Committee and the Compensation Committee&#146;s compensation consultant, the Board reviews the compensation paid to directors at companies in the current peer group
to determine whether any changes to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation are warranted. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As a result of its review in
December 2016, the Board increased the annual restricted stock unit (&#147;RSU&#148;) award from $135,000 to $150,000 and increased the annual Governance Committee Chair retainer from $10,000 to $15,000. The Board increased the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director stock ownership guidelines, as described below, from four times the annual retainer to five times the annual retainer. In addition, on February 22, 2017, in anticipation of Mr. Bilbrey&#146;s
transition to the role of Non-Executive Chairman of the Board, and upon the recommendation of the Compensation Committee, the Board approved an annual retainer of $150,000 for the Chairman of the Board position, to be paid in addition to the annual
retainer for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Accordingly, compensation paid to
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors in 2017 was as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="76%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">only when Chairman of the Board is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="11%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Paid</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">in addition to $100,000 annual retainer for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board completed its annual review of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation in December 2017 and determined that the
following changes were warranted for 2018 to ensure that the program remains </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">30 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">
aligned to the 50<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> percentile of compensation paid to directors from our 2017 Peer Group. The Board elected to increase the annual RSU award
from $150,000 to $155,000 and to increase the annual Audit Committee Chair retainer from $15,000 to $20,000. Except for these changes, all other elements of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation program
described above remain unchanged for 2018. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Payment of Annual Retainer, Lead Independent Director Fee and Committee Chair Fees
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The annual retainer and any applicable
Lead Independent Director or committee chair fees for all <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors are paid in quarterly installments on the 15<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th </SUP>day of March, June,
September and December, or the prior business day if the 15<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> is not a business day. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors may elect to receive all or a portion of the
annual retainer in cash or in Common Stock. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors may also elect to defer receipt of all or a portion of the retainer, Lead Independent Director fee or committee chair fees until the date
their membership on the Board ends. Lead Independent Director and committee chair fees that are not deferred are paid only in cash. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors choosing to defer all or a portion of their retainer, Lead Independent Director fee or committee chair fees may invest the deferred amounts in two ways: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In a cash account that values the performance of the investment based upon the performance of one or more third-party investment funds selected by the director from among the mutual funds or other investment options
available to all employees participating in our 401(k) Plan. Amounts invested in the cash account are paid only in cash. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In a deferred common stock unit account that we value according to the performance of our Common Stock, including reinvested dividends. Amounts invested in the deferred common stock unit account are paid in shares of
Common Stock. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Restricted Stock Units </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">RSUs are granted quarterly to <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors on the first day of January, April, July and October. In 2017, the number of RSUs granted in each quarter was determined by dividing $37,500 by the average closing price of a share of our
Common Stock on the New York Stock Exchange (&#147;NYSE&#148;) on the last three trading days preceding the grant date. RSUs awarded to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors vest one year after the date of grant, or earlier
upon termination of the director&#146;s membership on the Board by reason of retirement (termination of service from the Board after the director&#146;s 60<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> birthday), death or disability, for
any reason after a Change in Control as defined in our Executive Benefits Protection Plan (Group 3A) (&#147;EBPP 3A&#148;), or under such other circumstances as the Board may determine. Vested RSUs are payable to directors in shares of Common Stock
or, at the option of the director, can be deferred as common stock units under the Directors&#146; Compensation Plan until the director&#146;s membership on the Board ends. Dividend equivalent units are credited at regular rates on the RSUs during
the restriction period and, upon vesting of the RSUs, are payable in shares of Common Stock or deferred as common stock units together with any RSUs the director has deferred. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As of March&nbsp;5, 2018, Messrs. Bilbrey, Brown, Davis, Malcolm, Mead, Ridge and Shedlarz and Mmes.&nbsp;Arway, Haben and Koken had attained retirement age
for purposes of the vesting of RSUs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Other Compensation, Reimbursements and Programs </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board occasionally establishes committees of
limited duration for special purposes. When a special committee is established, the Board will determine whether to provide <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors with additional compensation for service on such committee
based on the expected duties of the committee, the anticipated number and length of any committee meetings, and other factors the Board, in its discretion, may deem relevant. No such committees were established in 2017. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">31 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We reimburse our directors for travel and other <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">out-of-pocket</FONT></FONT> expenses they incur when attending Board and committee meetings and for minor incidental expenses they incur when performing directors&#146; services. We also provide reimbursement for at least
one director continuing education program each year. Directors receive travel accident insurance while traveling on the Company&#146;s business and receive discounts on the purchase of our products to the same extent and on the same terms as our
employees. Directors also are eligible to participate in the Company&#146;s Gift Matching Program. Under the Gift Matching Program, the Company will match, upon a director&#146;s request, contributions made by the director to one or more charitable
organizations, on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">dollar-for-dollar</FONT></FONT> basis up to a maximum aggregate contribution of $5,000 annually. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Stock Ownership Guidelines </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Pursuant to the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance
Guidelines, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors are expected to own shares of Common Stock having a value equal to at least five times the annual retainer. Each <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director
has until January&nbsp;1 of the year following his or her fifth anniversary of becoming a director to satisfy the guideline. The Compensation Committee reviews the stock ownership guidelines annually to ensure they are aligned with external market
comparisons. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>2017 Director Compensation </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following table and explanatory footnotes provide
information with respect to the compensation paid or provided to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors during 2017: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">*</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Director </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Information Regarding Our Controlling Stockholder </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In 1909, Milton S. and Catherine S. Hershey
established a trust having as its sole beneficiary Milton Hershey School, a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-profit</FONT> school for the full-time care and education of disadvantaged children located in Hershey, Pennsylvania. Hershey Trust
Company, a state-chartered trust company, is trustee of the Milton Hershey School Trust. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">36 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In its capacity as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust, Hershey Trust Company is our controlling
stockholder. In this capacity, it will have the right to cast 5.5% of all of the votes entitled to be cast on matters requiring the vote of the Common Stock voting separately and 81.3% of all of the votes entitled to be cast on matters requiring the
vote of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together. The board of directors of Hershey Trust Company, with the approval of the board of managers (governing body) of Milton Hershey School, decides how funds held by Hershey Trust
Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust, will be invested. The board of directors of Hershey Trust Company generally decides how shares of The Hershey Company held by Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School
Trust, will be voted. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As of the Record Date, Hershey Trust Company also held 149,500 shares of our Common Stock as investments. The board of directors or
management of Hershey Trust Company decides how these shares will be voted. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In all, Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust
and as direct owner of investment shares, will be entitled to vote 8,403,121 shares of our Common Stock and 60,612,012 shares of our Class&nbsp;B Common Stock at the Annual Meeting. Stated in terms of voting power, Hershey Trust Company will have
the right to cast 5.6% of all of the votes entitled to be cast on matters requiring the vote of the Common Stock voting separately and 81.3% of all of the votes entitled to be cast on matters requiring the vote of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B
Common Stock voting together at the Annual Meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our certificate of incorporation contains the following important provisions regarding our
Class&nbsp;B Common Stock: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All holders of Class&nbsp;B Common Stock, including Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for Milton Hershey School, may convert any of their Class&nbsp;B Common Stock shares into shares of our Common Stock at any time on a
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">share-for-share</FONT></FONT> basis. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All shares of Class&nbsp;B Common Stock will automatically be converted to shares of Common Stock on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">share-for-share</FONT></FONT> basis if Hershey
Trust Company, as trustee for Milton Hershey School, or any successor trustee, or Milton Hershey School, as appropriate, ceases to hold more than 50% of the total Class&nbsp;B Common Stock shares outstanding and at least 15% of the total Common
Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock shares outstanding. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We must obtain the approval of Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for Milton Hershey School, or any successor trustee, or Milton Hershey School, as appropriate, before we issue any Common Stock or take any other action
that would deprive Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for Milton Hershey School, or any successor trustee, or Milton Hershey School, as appropriate, of the ability to cast a majority of the votes on any matter where the Class&nbsp;B Common Stock is
entitled to vote, either separately as a class or together with any other class. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">37 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_15"></A>AUDIT COMMITTEE REPORT </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>To Our Stockholders: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The
Audit Committee is currently comprised of six directors, each of whom is considered independent under the NYSE Rules and the rules and regulations of the SEC. The Board has determined that each member of the Audit Committee is financially literate
and that each of Messrs. Mead, Palmer and Shedlarz and Ms.&nbsp;Schoppert qualifies as an &#147;audit committee financial expert,&#148; as that term is defined under the rules promulgated by the SEC. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our role as the Audit Committee is to assist the Board in its oversight of: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The integrity of the Company&#146;s financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Company&#146;s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The independent auditors&#146; qualifications and independence; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The performance of the independent auditors and the Company&#146;s internal audit function. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit
Committee operates under a written charter that was last reviewed by the Audit Committee on November&nbsp;30, 2017. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our duties as an Audit Committee
include overseeing the Company&#146;s management, internal auditors and independent auditors in their performance of the following functions, for which they are responsible: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Management </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Preparing the Company&#146;s financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Establishing effective financial reporting systems and internal controls and procedures; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reporting on the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Internal Audit Department </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Independently assessing management&#146;s system of internal controls and procedures; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reporting on the effectiveness of that system. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Independent Auditors </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Auditing the Company&#146;s financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Expressing an opinion about the financial statements&#146; conformity with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Annually auditing the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We meet
periodically with management, the internal auditors and independent auditors, independently and collectively, to discuss the quality of the Company&#146;s financial reporting process and the adequacy and effectiveness of the Company&#146;s internal
controls. Prior to the Company filing its Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2017 with the SEC, we also: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reviewed and discussed the audited financial statements with management and the independent auditors; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Discussed with the independent auditors the matters required to be discussed by applicable requirements of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board; </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">38 </P>

</DIV></Center>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Received the written disclosures and the letter from the independent auditors in accordance with applicable requirements of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board regarding the independent auditors&#146;
communications with the Audit Committee concerning independence; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Discussed with the independent auditors their independence from the Company. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We are not employees of the
Company and are not performing the functions of auditors or accountants. We are not responsible as an Audit Committee or individually to conduct &#147;field work&#148; or other types of auditing or accounting reviews or procedures or to set auditor
independence standards. In carrying out our duties as Audit Committee members, we have relied on the information provided to us by management and the independent auditors. Consequently, we do not assure that the audit of the Company&#146;s financial
statements has been carried out in accordance with generally accepted auditing standards, that the financial statements are presented in accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles or that the Company&#146;s auditors are in fact
&#147;independent.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Based on the reports and discussions described in this report, and subject to the limitations on our role and responsibilities as
an Audit Committee referred to above and in our charter, we recommended to the Board that the audited financial statements be included in the Company&#146;s Annual Report on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Form&nbsp;10-K</FONT> for the year ended
December&nbsp;31, 2017, filed with the SEC on February&nbsp;27, 2018. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:54%; text-indent:-2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Submitted by the Audit Committee:</B> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:54%; text-indent:-2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">David L. Shedlarz, Chair </P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_17"></A>PROPOSAL NO.
2&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;RATIFICATION OF APPOINTMENT </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>OF INDEPENDENT AUDITORS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:40pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="90%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#3f000b" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">The Board of Directors unanimously recommends that stockholders vote<BR><B>FOR
</B>ratification of the Audit Committee&#146;s appointment of<BR>Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young&nbsp;LLP as the Company&#146;s independent auditors for 2018</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit Committee has appointed Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as the Company&#146;s independent auditors for 2018. Although not
required to do so, the Board, upon the Audit Committee&#146;s recommendation, has determined to submit the Audit Committee&#146;s appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as our independent auditors to stockholders for ratification as a matter of
good corporate governance. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit Committee&#146;s appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as the Company&#146;s independent auditors for 2018 will
be considered ratified if a majority of the shares of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock (voting together without regard to class) present and entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting are voted for the proposal. If stockholders do not
ratify the appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as the Company&#146;s independent auditors for 2018, the Audit Committee will reconsider its appointment. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Representatives of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP will attend the Annual Meeting, will have the opportunity to make a statement, if they so desire, and will
respond to questions. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">41 </P>

</DIV></Center>
