<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">On May&nbsp;2, 2017, Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day was appointed Senior Vice President, Chief Product Supply and Technology Officer. Previously, he served as the Senior Vice President, Chief Supply Chain Officer.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">On April&nbsp;3, 2017, Mr.&nbsp;Tillemans was hired as President, U.S. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">On May&nbsp;1, 2017, Ms.&nbsp;West was hired as Senior Vice President, Chief Growth Officer. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">On March&nbsp;1, 2017, Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey retired from the position of President and CEO. He continues to serve as Chairman of the Board, but he is not standing for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> at
the Annual Meeting. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_50"></A>Executive Summary </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><I>2017 Highlights
</I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Hershey Company (the &#147;Company&#148;), headquartered in Hershey, Pa., is a global confectionery leader known for bringing goodness to
the world through its chocolate, sweets, mints and other great-tasting snacks. We have approximately 16,910 employees around the world who work every day to deliver delicious, quality products. We have more than 80 brands that drive approximately
$7.5&nbsp;billion in annual revenues. Building on its core business, the Company is expanding its portfolio to include a broader range of delicious snacks. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In February 2017, we announced the following Company expectations, which are substantially reflected in our 2017 incentive programs: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Increase net sales between 2% to 3% from 2016; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Increase adjusted earnings per share-diluted<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> between 7% to 9% from 2016. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000;width:21%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">While we report our financial results in accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles (&#147;GAAP&#148;), we also use <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measures within
Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis in the 2017 Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> that accompanies this Proxy Statement in order to provide additional information to investors to facilitate the comparison of
past and present performance. Some of the financial targets under our short- and long-term incentive programs are also based on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measures. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-GAAP</FONT>
financial measures are used by management in evaluating results of operations internally and in assessing the impact of known trends and uncertainties on our business, but they are not intended to replace the presentation of financial results in
accordance with GAAP. Adjusted earnings per share-diluted is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measure. We define adjusted earnings per share-diluted as diluted earnings per share of the Company&#146;s common stock
(&#147;Common Stock&#148;), excluding unallocated <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">mark-to-market</FONT></FONT> (gains) losses on commodity derivatives, costs associated with business realignment activities, costs
relating to the integration of acquisitions, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-service</FONT> related components of our pension expense (&#147;NSRPE&#148;), goodwill, indefinite and long-lived asset impairment charges, settlement of the Shanghai
Golden Monkey liability in conjunction with the purchase of the remaining 20% of the outstanding shares of Shanghai Golden Monkey, the gain realized on the sale of a trademark, costs associated with the early extinguishment of debt and other
non-recurring gains and losses. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">42 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Actual results for 2017 were as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g498129g82a23.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Because we did not meet our expectations, our NEOs earned significantly below-target performance stock unit
(&#147;PSU&#148;) payouts and slightly below-target annual cash incentive awards, further reinforcing our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> philosophy. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><I>Hershey Has Strong <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Pay-for-Performance</FONT></FONT> Alignment
</I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation and Executive Organization Committee (the &#147;Compensation Committee&#148;) of our Board of Directors (the
&#147;Board&#148;) has oversight responsibility for our executive compensation framework and for aligning our executives&#146; pay with the Company&#146;s performance. We believe we have a strong <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> alignment because a significant portion of each NEO&#146;s target total direct compensation is tied to the financial performance of the Company as well as shareholder returns. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In 2017, approximately 68% of our CEO&#146;s and 60% of our other NEOs&#146; target total direct compensation, excluding Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s, was tied to
Company performance, including a substantial portion tied to shareholder value. Specifically, 34% of our PSUs were tied to Total Shareholder Return (&#147;TSR&#148;). Combined with the other financial and strategic metrics that determine our
NEOs&#146; compensation, we have aligned our executive compensation program with the long-term interests of our stockholders. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Over the last three years,
we have delivered a TSR of 17.4%, which is at the 20<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> percentile of our 2015 peer group described in the section entitled &#147;Performance Stock Unit Targets and Results.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g498129g74l68.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">43 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Because our TSR metric was below threshold for the 2015-2017 PSU cycle, our NEOs received a 0% payout for
this metric, significantly reducing their overall PSU payout, as described in more detail in the section entitled &#147;Performance Stock Unit Targets and Results.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><I>Our Stockholders Strongly Approve of Our Pay Practices </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Last year, our stockholders overwhelmingly approved our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;say-on-pay&#148;</FONT></FONT>
resolution, with more than 95% of the votes cast by the holders of Common Stock and more than 99% of the combined votes cast by the holders of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting in favor. Our Compensation Committee believes the
results of last year&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;say-on-pay&#148;</FONT></FONT> vote affirmed our stockholders&#146; support of our Company&#146;s executive compensation program. Consequentially,
our approach to executive compensation in 2017 was substantially the same as the approach stockholders approved in 2016. At the 2017 Annual Meeting of Stockholders, our stockholders voted to continue having an annual
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;say-on-pay&#148;</FONT></FONT> vote as described in Proposal No.&nbsp;3&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;Advise on Named Executive Officer Compensation. We plan to ask stockholders to express a
preference for the frequency of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;say-on-pay&#148;</FONT></FONT> vote at our 2023 Annual Meeting of Stockholders. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We believe our compensation and governance policies and practices are significant drivers of our stockholder support. These policies and practices include:
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Pay for performance.</B> A substantial percentage of each of our NEO&#146;s target total direct compensation is variable, performance-based compensation. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Performance measures support strategic objectives.</B> The performance measures we use for our variable, performance-based compensation reflect strategic and operating objectives, creating long-term value for our
stockholders. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Appropriate risk-taking.</B> We set performance goals that consider our publicly-announced financial expectations, which we believe will encourage appropriate risk taking. Our incentive programs are appropriately
capped so as not to encourage excessive risk taking. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>No tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups.</FONT></B> We generally do not provide tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups,</FONT> except for relocation expenses. In 2017, we provided a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-up</FONT> payment to Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey to provide him with benefits to which he was entitled under the terms of his retirement agreement. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>&#147;Double-trigger&#148; benefits in the event of a change in control.</B> In the event of a change in control, the payment of severance benefits and the acceleration of vesting of time-based long-term incentive
awards are &#147;double-trigger&#148; benefits. The severance payments and accelerated vesting of continuing incentive awards will not occur unless there is also a qualifying termination of employment upon or within two years following the change in
control. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>No <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-pricings</FONT> or exchanges of underwater stock options.</B> Our stockholder-approved Equity and Incentive Compensation Plan (&#147;EICP&#148;) prohibits <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-pricing</FONT> or exchange of underwater stock options without stockholder approval. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Do not provide excessive perquisites. </B>Executive perquisites are kept to a minimal level relative to a NEO&#146;s total compensation and do not play a significant role in our executive compensation program.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Do not provide for the prepayment of dividends on unearned PSUs. </B>Dividends are not paid on PSU awards during the three-year performance cycle. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Significant stock ownership guidelines.</B> Our NEOs and other executives are required to accumulate and hold stock equal to a multiple of base salary. If an executive has not met his or her ownership requirement in
a timely manner, the executive is required to retain a portion of shares received under long-term incentive awards until the requirements are met. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Anti-hedging policy.</B> Our NEOs, directors and other insiders are prohibited from entering into hedging transactions related to our stock. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Anti-pledging policy.</B> Our NEOs, directors and other insiders are prohibited from entering into pledging transactions related to our stock. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">44 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Clawbacks and other covenants. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"></SUP>For the protection of the Company, we require our NEOs to enter into an Employee Confidentiality and Restrictive Covenant Agreement (&#147;ECRCA&#148;) as a condition
of receipt of long-term incentive awards. Failure to comply with the ECRCA may subject the employee to cancellation of awards and a requirement to repay amounts received from awards. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"></SUP>Under the EICP, when an individual&#146;s actions result in the filing of financial documents not in compliance with financial reporting requirements, the Company has
the right to recoup or require repayment of an award earned or accrued during the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">12-month</FONT> period following the first public issuance or filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (&#147;SEC&#148;) of
the financial document not in compliance with such financial reporting requirement. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_20"></A>The
Role and Philosophy of the Compensation Committee </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee has primary responsibility for making compensation decisions for our NEOs other than our CEO. Our CEO&#146;s compensation is
approved by the independent members of the Board based on the recommendations of the Compensation Committee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee operates under a
charter approved by the Board. The Compensation Committee uses information from Mercer&nbsp;(US)&nbsp;Inc. (&#147;Mercer&#148;), the Compensation Committee&#146;s independent executive compensation consultant, input from our CEO (except for matters
regarding her own pay) and assistance from our Human Resources Department to make decisions and to conduct its annual review of the Company&#146;s executive compensation program. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee works with a rolling agenda, with its heaviest workload occurring during the first quarter of the year. During this quarter,
decisions are made with respect to annual and long-term incentives earned based on the prior year&#146;s performance and target compensation levels are finalized for the current year. The Compensation Committee also reviews and approves this
Compensation Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis. During the second and third quarters, the Compensation Committee reviews materials relating to peer group composition, tally sheets, competitive pay analysis and other information that forms the
foundation for future decisions. The Compensation Committee uses the third and fourth quarters to finalize decisions relating to the peer group and compensation plan design for use in the upcoming year. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee may, in its discretion, delegate all or a portion of its duties and responsibilities to a subcommittee of the Compensation Committee
and, pursuant to the provisions of the EICP, may appoint the CEO as a committee of the Board as necessary for the purpose of making equity grants under the EICP; provided, however, the Compensation Committee may not delegate the approval of certain
transactions to a subcommittee or to the CEO if such transactions involve the approval or grant of equity-based compensation to an &#147;officer&#148; for purposes of Rule <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16b-3</FONT> under the Securities Exchange
Act of 1934 (&#147;Exchange Act&#148;) or a &#147;covered employee&#148; for purposes of Section&nbsp;162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code (&#147;IRC&#148;) unless such subcommittee consists solely of members of the Compensation Committee who are (i)
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;Non-Employee</FONT> Directors&#148; for the purposes of Rule <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16b-3</FONT> under the Exchange Act, and (ii) &#147;outside directors&#148; for the purposes of Section&nbsp;162(m)
of the IRC. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">45 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The philosophy of our executive compensation program is to provide a compelling, dynamic, market-based total
compensation program tied to performance and aligned with our stockholders&#146; interests. Our goal is to ensure the Company has the talent it needs to maintain sustained long-term performance for our stockholders, employees and communities. The
guiding principles that help us achieve this goal are: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Recruit and retain. </B>Our program is designed to be market competitive and flexible to recruit and retain top talent for our critical roles. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Pay for performance.</B> A significant portion of our executives&#146; compensation is tied to the performance of our Company, rewarding executives for both short-term and long-term progress towards our strategic and
operational goals. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Aligned with strategy.</B> Our compensation program is aligned with the strategies of our Company. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Aligned with stockholders.</B> Our compensation program, through both design and payouts, is aligned with the long-term interests of our stockholders. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Reinforce robust succession planning.</B> Our compensation program plays a key role in making sure we have the talent we need for long-term success and to deliver our Company strategies. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Data-driven decision making.</B> We design our executive compensation program and make pay decisions considering a balance of information. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><I>Compensation Advisor Independence </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Under its engagement letter with the Compensation Committee, Mercer has acknowledged that the firm is retained by and performs its services for the
Compensation Committee while working with management to provide advice, counsel and recommendations that reinforce the Company&#146;s business strategy, economics, organization and management style. Mercer has provided and continues to provide
services and products to the Company in addition to its work for the Compensation Committee, including services related to global compensation consulting and surveys for various geographies. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee reviews all fees for services related to executive and director compensation provided by Mercer to the Compensation Committee, as
well as fees for compensation-related products and services provided to the Company. Fees paid to Mercer and its affiliates for services provided in 2017 related to executive and director compensation and compensation-related products and services
totaled $407,253 and $101,348, respectively. The decision to engage Mercer for compensation-related products and services was made by management. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The
Compensation Committee also received and discussed with Mercer its letter to the Compensation Committee addressing factors relevant under the SEC and New York Stock Exchange (&#147;NYSE&#148;) rules in assessing Mercer&#146;s independence from
management and whether Mercer&#146;s work for the Compensation Committee has raised any conflicts of interest, as well as Mercer&#146;s belief that no conflict of interest exists and that it serves as an independent advisor to the Compensation
Committee. The factors addressed included the extent of any business or personal relationships with any member of the Compensation Committee or any executive officer of the Company; Mercer&#146;s and its affiliates&#146; provision of other services
to the Company; the level of fees received from the Company as a percentage of total revenue of each of Mercer and Mercer&#146;s parent company; the policies and procedures employed by Mercer to avoid conflicts of interest; and any ownership of
Company stock by individuals employed by Mercer to advise the Compensation Committee. The Compensation Committee considered these factors before selecting or receiving advice from Mercer, and after considering these and other factors in their
totality, the Compensation Committee identified no conflicts of interest with respect to Mercer&#146;s advice. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">46 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In establishing compensation levels and awards for executive officers other than our CEO, the Compensation
Committee takes into consideration the recommendations of Mercer and the Human Resources Department, evaluations by our CEO of each officer&#146;s individual performance and Company performance. The Compensation Committee evaluates director
compensation primarily on the basis of peer group data used for benchmarking director compensation provided by Mercer. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_21">
</A>Compensation Components </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our
executive compensation program includes the following key elements: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>

 COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Key 2017 Actions</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Base Salary</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Fixed compensation component. Reviewed annually and adjusted as appropriate.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Intended to attract and retain executives with proven skills and leadership abilities that will enable us to be successful.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mmes. Buck and Little received an increase at the beginning of the year consistent
with how the Company sets compensation as described below.<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1) </SUP>Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day received an increase upon assuming expanded responsibilities in May 2017.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Annual Incentive Award</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Variable, performance-based compensation component. Payable based on business results and individual performance.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Intended to motivate and reward executives for successful execution of strategic priorities.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Targets as a percentage of base salary were established at the beginning of 2017 for
each NEO and at the time of hire for Mr.&nbsp;Tillemans and Ms.&nbsp;West.<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1) </SUP>Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day&#146;s target was subsequently increased upon assuming expanded responsibilities in May 2017. The
plan design remained consistent with the previous year.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Long-Term
Incentive Awards</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Variable compensation component. Granted annually as a combination of Restricted Stock Units
(&#147;RSUs&#148;), PSUs and stock options. PSUs and stock options are considered to be performance-based; the value of amounts actually earned depend on Company and stock price performance.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">Intended to motivate and reward executives for long-term Company financial performance and enhanced long-term stockholder value by balancing compensation opportunity and risk, while
encouraging sustained performance and retention.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>

and Ms.&nbsp;West. The plan design remained consistent with the previous year.</TD></TR>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following charts illustrate the weighting of base salary, annual incentive awards and long-term
incentive awards at target for our CEO and our other NEOs, excluding Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey, during 2017: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g498129g20c50.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_22"></A>Setting Compensation </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee&#146;s annual compensation
review for 2017 included an analysis of data, comparing the Company&#146;s executive and director compensation levels against a peer group of publicly-held consumer products companies. Mercer provides the Compensation Committee with advice, counsel
and recommendations with respect to the composition of the peer group and competitive data used for benchmarking our compensation program. The Compensation Committee uses this and other information provided by Mercer to reach an independent
recommendation regarding compensation to be paid to our CEO, directors and other officers. The Compensation Committee&#146;s final recommendation is then given to the independent directors of our Board for review and final approval. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Companies in the peer group used to benchmark executive and director pay levels for 2017 (the &#147;2017 Peer Group&#148;) are: </P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Molson Coors Brewing Company</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Dean Foods Company</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mondelez International</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Dr Pepper Snapple Group, Inc.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Clorox Company</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">General Mills, Inc.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The J. M. Smucker Company</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee selected these companies after reviewing publicly-held companies offering products/services similar
to ours, with annual revenues within a range of approximately <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-half</FONT> to two and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-half</FONT> times our annual revenue (with the exception of Mondelez International whom we
also consider a peer company for executive talent) and market capitalization within a reasonable range of our market capitalization. The 2017 Peer Group was composed of companies with annual revenues ranging from $3.7&nbsp;billion to
$25.9&nbsp;billion (as of fiscal year 2016) and market capitalization ranging from $2.0&nbsp;billion to $67.8&nbsp;billion (as of December&nbsp;31, 2016). Hershey&#146;s fiscal year 2016 revenue of $7.4&nbsp;billion and December&nbsp;31, 2016 market
capitalization of $22.0&nbsp;billion were at the 48<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> and 66<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> percentiles, respectively. All of the companies in our 2017 Peer Group were
included in our 2016 peer group. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">48 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Data from the 2017 Peer Group was supplemented by composite data from consumer products companies ranging in
size from $3&nbsp;billion to $17&nbsp;billion in approximate annual sales. This information was included in three national surveys conducted by Aon Hewitt, Mercer and Willis Towers Watson. The survey composite data provided us with broader,
industry-specific information regarding pay levels at consumer products companies for our NEOs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee reviewed a report summarizing
compensation levels at the 25<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP>, 50<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> and 75<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> percentiles of the 2017 Peer Group and the
survey composite data for positions comparable to those held by each of our NEOs. The Compensation Committee also reviewed a report comparing the target total cash compensation (base salary plus target annual incentive) and target total direct
compensation (base salary plus target annual incentive plus target long-term incentive) for each of the NEOs against these benchmarks. Hershey targets total direct compensation for its executive officers, in aggregate, at competitive pay levels
using the median of our peer group for reference. Positioning varies by job, and the Committee considers a number of factors including market competitiveness, specific duties and responsibilities of the executive versus those of peers, experience
and succession planning. The Committee believes it is appropriate to reward the executive management team with compensation above or below the competitive median if the financial targets associated with its variable pay programs are above or below
target, respectively. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">During 2017, the Compensation Committee received detailed tally sheets prepared by management. Each tally sheet captures
comprehensive compensation, benefits and stock ownership data. The tally sheets provide the Compensation Committee with a complete picture of each executive&#146;s current and projected compensation and the amount of each element of compensation or
other benefit the executive would receive in the event of voluntary or involuntary termination, retirement, disability, death, or upon change in control. The Compensation Committee considers this information, as well as the benchmark information,
when making compensation decisions. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_23"></A>Base Salary </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Base salary is the largest fixed component of our
executive compensation program and is determined by considering the relative importance of the position, the competitive marketplace and the individual&#146;s performance, responsibilities and experience. Salary reviews are generally conducted
annually at the beginning of the year. Each NEO&#146;s base salary is compared to internal and external references. Base salary adjustments, if any, are made after considering market references, Company performance against financial goals and
individual performance. CEO performance is evaluated by the Compensation Committee and independent members of the Board. The CEO evaluates the performance of her direct reports, including all NEOs, and reviews her recommendations for salary
adjustments with the Compensation Committee prior to its approval of the base salary for each NEO. If a NEO has responsibility for a particular business unit, the business unit&#146;s financial results also will be strongly considered. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">49 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On the basis of the foregoing considerations, the Compensation Committee, and all independent directors in
the case of our CEO, approved base salaries for 2017 as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

base salary through February&nbsp;28, 2017. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">See Column&nbsp;(c) of the 2017 Summary Compensation Table for information regarding the base
salary earned by each of our NEOs during 2017. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_24"></A>Annual Incentives </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our NEOs are eligible to receive an annual cash
incentive award under the One Hershey Incentive Program (&#147;OHIP&#148;), a program established under our EICP. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The OHIP links the NEO&#146;s payout
opportunity to measures he or she can affect most directly. For 2017, our CEO and all employees reporting directly to her, including the NEOs, had common financial objectives tied to total Company performance consistent with their responsibility to
manage the entire Company. Total Company performance targets are established in the context of our announced expectations for financial performance, prior year results and market conditions. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">50 </P>

</DIV></Center>

<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000;width:21%">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Ms.&nbsp;Buck is based on a base salary of $1,036,731, reflecting her target base salary both before and after the March increase. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>

for Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day is based on a base salary of $605,480, reflecting his target base salary both before and after the May increase. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Mr.&nbsp;Tillemans was hired as President, U.S. effective April&nbsp;3, 2017. The percent of target total direct compensation for Mr.&nbsp;Tillemans is based on a base salary of $456,731, reflecting his target base
salary from his hire date through December&nbsp;31, 2017. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Ms.&nbsp;West was hired as Senior Vice President, Chief Growth Officer effective May&nbsp;1, 2017. The percent of target total direct compensation for Ms.&nbsp;West is based on a base salary of $425,000, reflecting her
target base salary from her hire date through December&nbsp;31, 2017. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">On March&nbsp;1, 2017, Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey retired from the position of President and CEO. The percent of target total direct compensation for Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey is based on a base salary of $223,431, reflecting his target
base salary through February&nbsp;28, 2017. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In determining the target OHIP percentage for each of the NEOs, the Compensation Committee, and
the independent directors in the case of our CEO, considered the value of target total cash compensation against market references. Target total cash compensation levels for each of the NEOs fall within an appropriate range relative to the median
for comparable positions given each incumbent&#146;s performance, responsibilities and tenure in the role. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In general, the final OHIP award is determined
by multiplying the NEO&#146;s base salary, the applicable target percentage and performance scores ranging from 0% to 200% based on Company and individual performance. The Company performance goals are established at the beginning of each year by
the Compensation Committee. Individual performance goals also are established at that time, or at the time of hire if later. If performance scores exceed the target objectives, a NEO may receive an OHIP payout greater than his or her target award
value. If performance scores are below the target objectives, the NEO&#146;s OHIP payout will be below his or her target award value, subject to no award if performance is below threshold levels. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">For 2017, Company financial performance metrics accounted for 65% of each NEO&#146;s target award under the program. The remaining 35% was based upon
individual performance toward achievement of up to six individual performance goals focused on strategic priorities applicable to the NEO&#146;s position, but tied to the overall Company&#146;s top priorities for the year. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><I>2017 OHIP Performance Targets and Results </I></FONT></P>

year period for entities reporting in currencies other than the U.S. dollar are translated into U.S. dollars at the average rates during the comparable period of the prior fiscal year. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Adjusted earnings per share-diluted is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> performance measure. For more information regarding how we define adjusted earnings per share-diluted, please see footnote
(1)&nbsp;in the section entitled &#147;Executive Summary.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Operating cash flow is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> performance measure. We define operating cash flow as the average of cash from operations less certain
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-time</FONT> items impacting comparability. For more information regarding our use of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> performance measures, please see footnote (1)&nbsp;in the section entitled
&#147;Executive Summary.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We achieved below-target performance in net sales and adjusted earnings&nbsp;per&nbsp;share-diluted and
above-target performance in operating cash flow. As a result, 65% of the 2017 OHIP award for each NEO was based on the Company performance score of 97.90%. The remainder of the OHIP award was determined by individual performance ratings. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Michele G. Buck, President and CEO </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">At the beginning of 2017, Ms.&nbsp;Buck served as our Executive Vice President, COO. On March&nbsp;1, 2017, Ms.&nbsp;Buck was promoted to President and CEO.
Her goals and evaluation reflected both roles. Ms.&nbsp;Buck was responsible for strategic leadership and delivery of the Company&#146;s financial objectives, portfolio expansion to drive future growth, building critical capabilities and improving
the Company&#146;s operations. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Patricia A. Little, Senior Vice President, CFO </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The individual performance goals for Ms.&nbsp;Little focused on enabling profitable growth through acquisition, delivering continued process improvements,
delivering on our strategic plan and continuing to build global financial capability. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Terence L. O&#146;Day, Senior
Vice President, Chief Product Supply and Technology Officer </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The individual performance goals for Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day focused on delivering an
agile supply chain network to fuel margins and enable growth, driving transformation of a simplified enterprise operating model and delivering a contemporized technology system to support enterprise goals. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Todd W. Tillemans, President, U.S. </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The individual performance goals for Mr.&nbsp;Tillemans focused on maximizing the impact of commercial investments in the core confection business, delivering
customer service levels, building capability within the commercial organization and achieving the financial objectives for the U.S. market. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">52 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Mary Beth West, Senior Vice President, Chief Growth Officer </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The individual performance goals for Ms.&nbsp;West focused on developing a growth strategy and roadmap, unlocking growth on core brands, building marketing
capability and enabling profitable growth through acquisition. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>J. P. Bilbrey, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board and Former President and CEO
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On March&nbsp;1, 2017, Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey retired from the position of President and CEO. He has continued to serve as <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board. The individual performance goals for Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey during his time as President and CEO centered on delivery of the Company&#146;s financial goals, strategic leadership and
succession planning. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Overall Results </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Following
the close of 2017, the Compensation Committee provided the independent directors with an assessment of Ms.&nbsp;Buck&#146;s and Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s 2017 performance and achievement relative to their respective individual performance goals. Our
financial results were around target despite challenging industry conditions in the category. Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey delivered on his strategic leadership and succession planning objectives, including a successful transition of the CEO role. Ms.&nbsp;Buck
also delivered on her strategic leadership goals, including advancing the strategic direction of the company, enabling continued growth through portfolio expansion, improving the international business and upgrading talent and capabilities in
critical areas. Based upon those assessments, the Compensation Committee recommended, and the Board approved, the individual performance awards and total OHIP payouts for Ms.&nbsp;Buck and Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey as shown in the table below. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Ms.&nbsp;Buck provided the Compensation Committee with her assessment of each NEO&#146;s 2017 performance and achievement in relation to their performance
goals. Based upon those assessments, Ms.&nbsp;Buck recommended, and the Compensation Committee approved, the individual performance awards and total OHIP payouts as shown in the table below. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Based upon a 65% weight for the Company financial score of 97.90% of target and a 35% weight for the individual performance award, our NEOs earned the
following 2017 OHIP awards: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The 2017 OHIP payments are included in Column&nbsp;(g) of the 2017 Summary Compensation Table for each NEO.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc498129_25"></A>Long-Term Incentives </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We provide long-term incentive opportunities to
motivate, retain and reward our NEOs for their contributions to multi-year performance in achieving strategies and improving long-term share value. In February of each year, the Compensation Committee awards long-term incentive grants, including
PSUs, stock options and RSUs, to our NEOs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee, and the independent directors in the case of our CEO, determines the value of
long-term incentive awards made to each NEO by considering the NEO&#146;s target total direct compensation against internal and external references. The target award percentages approved in February&nbsp;2017, or at the time of hire for
Mr.&nbsp;Tillemans and Ms.&nbsp;West, expressed as a percentage of base salary, were: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee values RSUs and PSUs using the closing stock price of the Company&#146;s Common Stock on the NYSE on the date of grant. The
Compensation Committee values stock options using the value of the stock options at the date of grant as determined for financial reporting purposes (the Black-Scholes value). Target total direct compensation levels for each of the NEOs fall within
an appropriate range relative to the median for comparable positions given each incumbent&#146;s, performance, responsibilities and tenure in the role. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">54 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><I>Performance Stock Unit Targets and Results </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">PSUs are granted to NEOs and other executives in a position to affect the Company&#146;s long-term results. At the start of each three-year cycle, a contingent
target number of PSUs is established for each executive. This target is expressed as a percentage of the executive&#146;s base salary and is determined as part of a total compensation package based on the peer group and survey composite benchmarks.
The PSU award generally represents approximately <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-half</FONT> of the recipient&#146;s long-term incentive compensation target award. Dividends are not paid on PSU awards during the three-year performance cycle.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><U>2015-2017 PSU Award </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The
performance objectives for the 2015-2017 performance cycle awarded in 2015 were based upon the following metrics: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Three-year relative TSR versus the 2015 peer group described below; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Three-year compound annual growth rate (&#147;CAGR&#148;) in organic net sales outside the United States and Canada; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Three-year CAGR in adjusted earnings&nbsp;per&nbsp;share-diluted measured against an internal target; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Annual (as opposed to three-year) growth in adjusted earnings&nbsp;per&nbsp;share-diluted measured against an internal target for each year of the three-year performance cycle. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee selected these metrics to measure performance against internal targets aligned with our stockholders&#146; interests and investment
returns offered by our peer companies. The 2015 peer group originally included 15 companies with median revenues of $8.1&nbsp;billion. Kraft Foods Group was subsequently removed from the 2015 peer group as a result of a corporate transaction.
Therefore, 14 companies remained in the 2015-2017 cycle for use in assessing our Company&#146;s 2015-2017 TSR. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Companies included in the 2015 peer group
for the 2015-2017 PSU cycle award were: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee approved the annual adjusted earnings&nbsp;per&nbsp;share-diluted target for each year of the
three-year performance cycle at the beginning of the performance year. Payment of any amounts earned, including amounts based on the annual performance goals, will be made in shares of our Common Stock at the conclusion of the three-year performance
cycle. The maximum award for any participant in a performance cycle is 250% of the contingent target award. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">55 </P>

</DIV></Center>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">56 </P>
